description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for two Band 6 Senior Tissue Viability Nurse fixed term 1 yr contracts within our small but dynamic team. Full or part time hours are both an option and internal candidates may be able to negotiate a secondment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently redesigning our service to a more locality based model and are looking to recruit into these posts to support the roll out of this new way of working. Although we plan to work in localities we will still be a countywide-based service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for motivated and enthusiastic individuals who have a passion for tissue viability, delivering quality care and helping others to achieve the same. As a band 6 post we are seeking someone with well developed leadership skills and experience in either managing or supporting other clinicians in practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Although a formal tissue viability qualification is not essential, those considering the post will need to have had considerable experience of caring for patients with a wide range of wounds, be proactive in the prevention of avoidable skin breakdown, have the experience and confidence to be involved in both formal and informal teaching programs and should be prepared to be actively involved in the wide range of service improvement projects undertaken by the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ongoing training and personal development will be provided through a structured process of supervision and peer support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Penny Rubio&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Clinical Lead Tissue Viability&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: penny.rubio@oxfordhealth.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 07920233477&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Contact Lauren Corcoran on 07786190725 or email: Lauren.orcoran@oxfordhealth.nhs.uk or Julie Hewish on 07385417295 or email: julie.hewish@oxfordhealth.nhs.uk if you would like to discuss the role further.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately, due to current covid-19 restrictions an informal visit is not an option however we are happy to talk by phone or on Microsoft Teams if you wish.&lt;/p&gt;
